==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Celastrus
<hw>Celastrus</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>the type genus of the
<fam>Celastraceae</fam>, comprising the plants called <altname>climbing
bittersweet</altname>; bittersweet and shrubby bittersweet; they are
woody vines and shrubs native chiefly to Asia and Australia, bearing
yellow to orange capsules which open to expose red-coated seeds. See
also <er>bittersweet{3b}</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Celastrus</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Celature</ent>⟦br⟧
